h3#anatomy-post.counter-reset-numbers <strong>Post</strong> content

p <small>(Click the item below to reveal more info. Click the image to preview a bigger size.)</small>

+details( 'Featured image', 'anatomy-post-' )
	p It is recommended to <a href="https://codex.wordpress.org/Post_Thumbnails#Setting_a_Post_Thumbnail">set up a post featured image</a> for each post.
	p A featured image is displayed in posts listing and also in <a href="#page-intro">intro section</a> on a single post page.
	p Please see FAQ section for more <a href="#image-sizes">information on image sizes</a>.

+details( 'Post title and subtitle', 'anatomy-post-' )
	p Title of the post.
	p If you would like to display subtitles, use <a href="#wp-subtitle"><strong>WP Subtitle</strong> plugin</a>.
	p You can also display intro widgets here or hide the post intro section altogether using <a href="#page-templates">post type page templates</a>.

+details( 'Post excerpt', 'anatomy-post-' )
	p If you set a custom <a href="#posts">post excerpt</a>, it will be displayed in posts listing and in intro section on a single post page.

+details( 'Post meta', 'anatomy-post-' )
	p Such as post publish date, post author name, number of comments...

+details( 'Post content', 'anatomy-post-' )
	p A post content, optimized for readability. You can <a href="#formats">use "Formats" button</a> for some special styles.
	p You can also use a <a href="#beaver-builder">page builder</a> to create some interesting post layouts.

+details( 'Table of contents', 'anatomy-post-' )
	p If you separate a post into multiple parts, there will be a <a href="#posts">table of contents</a> automatically generated.

+details( 'Sharing buttons', 'anatomy-post-' )
	p To enable post, custom post and/or WooCommerce products sharing buttons (can be previewed on the <a href="https://themedemos.webmandesign.eu/icelander/">theme demo website</a>), please use <a href="#jetpack"><strong>Jetpack</strong></a> plugin's <a href="https://jetpack.com/support/sharing/">sharing module</a>.

+details( 'Comments', 'anatomy-post-' )
	p Comments are useful for blog posts to engage discussion with your website visitors. You can set them up in <strong><em>Settings &raquo; Discussion</em></strong> and disable them also per post basis.
	p However, if you do not want to use comments for specific post types, we recommend setting up <a href="#plugins-others"><strong>Disable Comments</strong> plugin</a>.

+details( 'Posts navigation', 'anatomy-post-' )
	p Displays links to previous and next post.

+details( 'Page builder', 'anatomy-post-' )
	p For creating a more interesting, complex post layouts please use a (<a href="#page-builder">any</a>) page builder plugin (we recommend using powerful, optimized and easy to use <a href="#beaver-builder"><strong>Beaver Builder</strong> page builder plugin</a>).
	p Please note that you will probably need to <strong>enable the page builder for WordPress posts</strong> first! (For Beaver Builder go to <strong><em>Settings &raquo; Page Builder &raquo; Post Types</em></strong>.)

+details( 'Sidebar', 'anatomy-post-' )
	p The theme displays sidebar on each single post page, blog page and archive page.
	p Sidebar is a <a href="#widgets">widgetized area</a>, its content can be set in <strong><em>Appearance &raquo; Customize &raquo; Widgets</em></strong>.
	p If you would like to replace sidebar on a specific post with a different one <strong>or just remove it</strong>, use <a href="#content-aware-sidebars"><strong>Content Aware Sidebars</strong> plugin</a>. It is a great way to control and alter your website layout.

+details( 'Content options', 'anatomy-post-' )
	p The theme is compatible with several content options provided by <a href="#jetpack"><strong>Jetpack</strong> plugin</a>. You can hide certain post meta information or display post author biography below post content.

